    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-25T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8648</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-25T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1382. I have just seen a copy of the secret treaty, April 25 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >26</hi>], 1915, between Italy, France, England and Russia; presume that you
                        <pb facs="0135" n="43" xml:id="pg_43"/> have seen it as it appeared in
                        Russia<note n="1" xml:id="d27fn1">See <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_497">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, Supplement 2, vol. I,
                            pp. 497</ref>–<ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_500">500</ref>.</note>
                    and in the English magazine <hi rend="italic">New Europe</hi>. It has not been
                    published in Italy nor, I believe, in France. Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_OVE1">Orlando</persName> has gone to England accompanied by
                    Minister of War and <persName>Crespi</persName>, Food Commissioner to Paris, to
                    seek a reaffirmation of this secret treaty in view of the speeches by the
                    President and <persName corresp="#p_LGD1">Lloyd George</persName>. It is
                    reported that <persName corresp="#p_OVE1">Orlando</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SBS1">Sonnino</persName> had a stiff quarrel; the latter refused
                    to go to England saying that he had the Allies’ written promise and he was
                    against discussing the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
